  "prompt": "What is the minimum level of mathematical proficiency required to graduate from West Point?",
  "response": "As of my latest update in October 2023, the United States Military Academy at West Point requires cadets to complete a rigorous academic curriculum that includes mathematics. The minimum level of mathematical proficiency required for graduation typically includes courses in calculus and probability and statistics. \n\nCadets are generally expected to complete:\n\n1. **Mathematical Modeling and Introduction to Calculus (MA103):** An introductory course covering fundamental concepts of calculus and its applications.\n2. **Calculus I (MA205):** A comprehensive study of differential and integral calculus.\n3. **Calculus II (MA206):** Continuation of Calculus I, focusing on advanced integration techniques, series, and multi-variable calculus.\n4. **Probability and Statistics (MA376):** Covers the fundamental principles of probability and statistics, essential for various applications in military science and engineering.\n\nAdditionally, depending on their chosen major or focus area, cadets might be required to take more advanced mathematics courses. The precise requirements can vary based on the specific academic program or major a cadet pursues.\n\nIt's important to note that these requirements may evolve, so for the most accurate and up-to-date information, you should refer directly to the United States Military Academy\u2019s academic catalog or contact their admissions office.",
